(OOC: Sorry I haven't been replying, I've got finals coming up and I have a 
lot of studying to do.)

Tavatron hesitated as she heard Dinobot's question. *Gestures? The last time 
she had been hunting all they had done was run through the woods screaming 
at the top of their lungs. No wonder they had come home empty handed.* 
Tavatron chuckled softly to herself as she remembered the constant bickering 
over who's fault the bad hunt had been.

However, this was neither the time nor the place to reminice about one's 
past. Tavatron sighed as she gazed into the forest, the light filtering 
through the upper leaves. Her fur was a perfect match, dark like the earth 
and brown like the trees.

Tavatron took a deep breath, she could do this. It was just a little hunt, 
no big deal. It was no different than the practice battle she and Dinobot 
had had a few days ago. Except this time they weren't hunting each other:

"I am ready." Tavatron begins to slowly move off deeper into the forest, 
every sensor at full as she gazed about the forest floor in search of prey.
